  "title": "RenewedMenu",
  "description": "It change the \"menu aspect\" of the game, enjoy",
  "body": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-size: 14px;\"><strong>RenewedMen&ugrave;</strong></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"color: #993300;\">What's is?</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #000000;\">This texture add a bunch of tweak and tips regarding </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #000000;\">the \"menu side\" of the game</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #800000;\">It change:</span></strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">All container GUIs</li>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">The buttons, making them more similar to those of the bedrock version&nbsp;</li>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #000000;\">Change the menu background</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #000000;\">The shulker boxes: their inventory changes color depending on the color of the shulker</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #000000;\">The background of the advancement menu</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #000000;\">The background of the main menu</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #800000;\">The main menu:</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The main menu as you will notice remains stationary, strange isn't it?<br />Well, I found that Minecraft can have static backgrounds, which can be changed! With all possible resolutions, there are no limits.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the texture there are already various images, pre-installed by me.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://i.redd.it/re4wjo0pzro81.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"295\" /><br />To change the background enter in the zip file and follow this path:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em style=\"font-size: 1.2rem;\">\"assets \\ minecraft \\ textures \\ gui \\ title \\ background\"</em><span style=\"font-size: 1.2rem;\">,</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">paste your image there and rename it \"<em>panorama_overlay</em>\"</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #800000;\">The shulker box:</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><img src=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/uploadrandomimage/comments/tjhm7s/e/?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=web2x&amp;context=3\" alt=\"\" width=\"Infinity\" /><img src=\"https://i.redd.it/sxmcvvnyyro81.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"527\" height=\"297\" /><br /></span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">They are colorful now.<br />Example: if you open a red-colored shulker, its inventory will take on its own color, and this for all 17 shulkers!</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">(Optifine required)</span></p>",
